Levitt Says Volcker Rule May Lose Some of Its Strength (Audio)

-- B y  
-- 
2011-10-13T13:27:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/levitt-says-volcker-rule-may-lose-some-of-its-strength-audio-.html
Arthur Levitt, former chairman of 
the Securities and Exchange Commission and an adviser to Goldman
Sachs, says the Volcker rule will not survive "in strong form" 
and banks may move away from being bank holding companies.  
Levitt talks with Bloomberg's Ken Prewitt and Tom Keene on 
Bloomberg Radio's "Bloomberg Surveillance."  (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 05:37
 